SIMPLE: pinnated
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pinnated
<hw>Pin"na*ted</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>pinnatus</ets> feathered, fr.
<ets>pinna</ets> a feather. See <er>Pin</er> a peg, <er>Pen</er>
feather.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Consisting of several
leaflets, or separate portions, arranged on each side of a common
petiole, as the leaves of a rosebush, a hickory, or an ash. See
<cref>Abruptly pinnate</cref>, and <xex>Illust.</xex>, under
<er>Abruptly</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having a winglike tuft of long
feathers on each side of the neck.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pinnated grouse</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the
prairie chicken.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pinnately</ent>⟦br⟧
